name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: ...SEC’s previous argument that Hinman’s speech was just a personal opinion. It can’t be protected if it was his personal opinion. But if protected as SEC’s opinion, then further strengthens Ripple argument on fair notice and similarity to BTC/ETH from speech. 17/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: This hurts Ripple b/c SEC will argue it was all related to 70+ year old Howey test already on the books. The Court did not rule on whether EPA had to disclose the briefing documents because its privilege log “did not clarify whether the information..." 13/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: Briefing Docs: This hurts Ripple the most. Court ruled that docs are predecisional and DPP “if it relates to a specific decision or a specific decisionmaking process and was generated before the conclusion of that decision or process.” The Court gave a harmful example: 11/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: More specifically, documents will be privileged if they “indicate whether these discussions concerned the agency’s decision of what to say about the policy or how to formulate that message.” How could this be applied to SEC v. Ripple? 8/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: But “records that are not related to the form and content of the communication will generally lie outside the scope of the privilege, even if those records were created while the agency was making its communications decision.” This is where SEC and Ripple will focus. 7/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: Also, remember DPP can be held to apply BUT OVERCOME if disclosure interests outweigh nondisclosure. The EPA case was a FOIA request, not a request by a company being sued by a govt agency for over $1B. A key difference that Ripple will emphasize and should carry some weight. 4/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: This case (NRC v. EPA) concerned FOIA request and was on a motion for summary judgment, meaning EPA case is in a diff circumstance than Ripple case. Regardless, DPP legal analysis will be the same. Was also a split decision, but more favorable ruling for Ripple was losing one. 2/

name: Fred Rispoli
tweet: Analysis on Ripple's chances after analysis of CORRECT case. TLDR: SEC can delay a ruling for at least 1-2 months and likely will succeed in getting many but not all documents deemed DPP but judge can still override DPP...1/ @JohnEDeaton1 @attorneyjeremy1 #XRPCommunity #XRP
